notes:
This is an area of mixed landscaping and natural flora, with park areas and trails winding around and through condominiums. The area extends from Page Mill Rd. at Peter Coutts Rd. at the Southeast corner to Peter Coutts Rd. at Stanford Ave. at the Northwest corner. The area running along the edge of Page Mill Rd. has many conifers and some mixed hardwoods which are easily accessed from Peter Coutts Rd at Page Mill Rd. That is an area of green belt which separated a condominuium complex from the roadway.  I think it is private land, but people walk or bike through parts of it on trails, which may be public easements.

notes:
Founded in 1960 with 39 acres including the museum, the park now includes most of London's holdings and is a National Historic Landmark.

The park's 1400 acres include the Beauty Ranch, Cottage, House of Happy Walls Museum, Wolf House ruins, and more than 20 miles of trails. The park is located in Glen Ellen, California, about 1.5 hours north of San Francisco, in Sonoma County between the towns of Sonoma and Santa Rosa.

The property covers land on the eastern slope of Sonoma Mountain.

The park has a $10 entry fee. Mushroom collecting is not allowed without a permit.

Predominant coverage is oak, fir, grassland, some madrone.
